<item>
            <title>[SPR-5931] Allow non-standard attributes in &lt;form&gt; tags</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-5931</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The dojo framework creates form widgets using a syntax like this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;		&amp;lt;select	dojoType=&quot;dijit.form.FilteringSelect&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
				id=&quot;setvaluetest2&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
				name=&quot;state1&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
				autoComplete=&quot;false&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
				invalidMessage=&quot;Invalid state name&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
				onChange=&quot;dojo.byId(&apos;oc1&apos;).value=arguments&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as I can tell, it&apos;s impossible to do stuff like this with the Spring &amp;lt;form&amp;gt; tags because there is no way to specify non-standard HTML attributes.  An approach I&apos;ve used for my own custom tags is to add a catch-all attribute called &quot;attributes&quot; so the syntax would look something like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;form:select id=&quot;setvaluetest2&quot; attributes=&apos;dojoType=&quot;dijit.form.FilteringSelect&quot; invalidMessage=&quot;Invalid state name&quot; ... etc&lt;/p&gt;</description>
